<kml>
<property-doc name=Maneuver-Effectiveness>
<system-documentation name=Maneuver-Effectiveness>
<gpd-documentation name=CritiqueScores>

<description>
Maneuver effectiveness is defined as the movement or placement of formations in a manner that produces maximum relative combat power advantage at the point of decision to achieve victory.
</description>

<example>
Maneuver effectiveness is the combination of many factors: skillful use of terrain, ease of command and control, logistical supportability, force security, use of deception, synchronization of fires and maneuver, proper use of reserve forces, use of available assets, exploitation of enemy vulnerabilities, timeliness, simplicity, and the generation of decisive relative combat power.
</example>

</kml>
